WEBVTT

01:37.080 --> 01:38.210
We want to talk here.

01:45.560 --> 01:46.440
Tell me now.

01:49.840 --> 01:50.720
Xiaoyue.

01:51.120 --> 01:53.520
I asked someone to take a message to the Manager,

01:53.520 --> 01:54.160
saying that I joined the army.

01:54.160 --> 01:55.220
Didn't he tell you?

01:59.800 --> 02:00.600
What's wrong?

02:02.200 --> 02:03.200
The Manager

02:04.640 --> 02:05.560
is dead.

02:05.640 --> 02:06.320
What?

02:07.240 --> 02:08.320
Dead?

02:11.800 --> 02:12.800
That night,

02:12.800 --> 02:14.000
in our room,

02:14.760 --> 02:17.480
Baozi and I were putting up double happiness papercuts.

02:17.480 --> 02:19.760
Suddenly, gunfire and artillery went off outside,

02:19.760 --> 02:21.490
and the street fell into chaos.

02:21.640 --> 02:22.440
Japanese planes

02:22.440 --> 02:24.079
started dropping bombs.

02:24.400 --> 02:26.660
The street was full of fleeing refugees.

02:27.320 --> 02:29.320
Not knowing where the bullets came from,

02:29.320 --> 02:31.650
people just suddenly fell as they walked.

02:32.280 --> 02:33.520
The Manager, Baozi, and I,

02:33.520 --> 02:34.800
we ran outside.

02:35.160 --> 02:36.020
Halfway there,

02:36.400 --> 02:38.360
the Manager insisted he hadn't taken his land deed

02:38.360 --> 02:39.560
and wanted to go back.

02:39.800 --> 02:40.560
He said

02:41.320 --> 02:42.600
he was afraid the fire would burn the house down

02:42.600 --> 02:44.260
and everything would be lost.

02:46.240 --> 02:47.040
And then?

02:48.440 --> 02:50.240
Then a bomb dropped

02:51.240 --> 02:52.720
and hit him.

02:54.120 --> 02:56.880
The fire burned all night,

02:57.600 --> 03:00.080
turning the whole sky red.

03:04.800 --> 03:05.920
So,

03:06.880 --> 03:07.920
our home

03:09.360 --> 03:10.440
is gone too.

03:13.920 --> 03:14.800
Gone.

03:16.480 --> 03:17.800
Everything is gone.

03:23.800 --> 03:26.480
I've been looking for you these days.

03:26.800 --> 03:27.960
Refugee camps, hospitals,

03:27.960 --> 03:28.920
I looked everywhere for you.

03:28.920 --> 03:30.800
I know. I know.

03:30.840 --> 03:32.160
I was just afraid you were on the street,

03:32.160 --> 03:33.480
hit by a stray bullet.

03:33.560 --> 03:35.000
What would I do?

03:35.200 --> 03:37.000
I know. I know.

03:37.160 --> 03:39.240
Don't cry. Don't cry.

03:40.880 --> 03:42.120
You are so timid

03:42.720 --> 03:43.780
and afraid of pain.

03:44.000 --> 03:46.260
Bullets on the battlefield have no eyes.

03:46.400 --> 03:48.640
What if you really get hurt?

03:48.880 --> 03:50.240
I don't want to be this...

03:50.240 --> 03:51.320
Um,

03:51.720 --> 03:54.160
I should call you sister-in-law, right?

03:56.360 --> 04:00.280
Your man is very brave on the battlefield.

04:01.360 --> 04:02.490
He's a good soldier.

04:03.360 --> 04:04.400
And

04:04.760 --> 04:06.000
he understands discipline

04:06.000 --> 04:07.260
and follows the rules.

04:07.320 --> 04:08.280
Right?

04:10.000 --> 04:10.880
Yes.

04:13.360 --> 04:14.920
Xiaoyue, don't worry.

04:15.240 --> 04:17.640
I'm not the kind of soldier who charges to the front.

04:17.640 --> 04:18.640
I hide in the back.

04:18.680 --> 04:19.760
I'm an orderly.

04:19.800 --> 04:20.760
I follow the officers.

04:20.760 --> 04:21.290
You know,

04:21.360 --> 04:22.280
on the battlefield,

04:22.280 --> 04:23.560
officers are the least likely to die.

04:23.560 --> 04:24.600
I just follow them.

04:24.600 --> 04:25.360
I'm very smart.

04:25.360 --> 04:25.720
Don't worry.

04:25.720 --> 04:26.800
I will definitely come back alive.

04:26.800 --> 04:28.120
I will

04:28.200 --> 04:30.120
definitely come back alive.

04:31.600 --> 04:32.400
Okay.

04:32.600 --> 04:34.530
I will definitely come back alive.

04:35.640 --> 04:37.500
Then you fight the Japanese well.

04:38.520 --> 04:40.180
I'll wait for you to come back.

04:44.680 --> 04:46.040
We have bad luck.

04:46.480 --> 04:48.880
God gave us a bad fate.

04:48.920 --> 04:50.800
Don't believe in fate, old man.

04:51.400 --> 04:53.200
Do you still resent heaven now?

04:53.800 --> 04:55.080
Heaven is empty.

04:55.280 --> 04:57.440
Who drove you out of your hometown

04:57.600 --> 04:59.480
and made it so you couldn't farm your land?

04:59.480 --> 05:00.360
And who

05:00.600 --> 05:01.920
made you homeless

05:02.200 --> 05:03.280
and starve?

05:03.760 --> 05:04.560
All of this

05:05.000 --> 05:06.880
is done by people.

05:07.080 --> 05:07.960
Yes.

05:08.320 --> 05:09.720
The ones who made us starve and suffer

05:09.720 --> 05:10.850
and made us homeless

05:10.960 --> 05:12.760
are the Japanese imperialists,

05:12.760 --> 05:14.920
and the non-resisting traitors.

05:15.240 --> 05:17.600
Everyone, unite,

05:18.000 --> 05:20.260
and let's bring down our enemy together!

05:20.360 --> 05:21.360
Friends,

05:21.920 --> 05:23.380
we have to stand together!

05:23.640 --> 05:25.720
We must seek revenge and fight against

05:25.720 --> 05:27.520
those who oppress and exploit us!

05:27.520 --> 05:29.400
Revenge and fight!

05:30.120 --> 05:31.980
We cannot forget September 18th!

05:32.040 --> 05:34.000
We cannot forget Lugou Bridge!

05:34.840 --> 05:36.880
The Chinese nation has reached

05:36.880 --> 05:38.360
its most perilous moment.

05:38.720 --> 05:40.920
We must be of one mind!

05:41.720 --> 05:44.800
Eliminate the Japanese and protect the country!

05:45.080 --> 05:48.040
Eliminate the Japanese and protect the country!

05:48.320 --> 05:51.050
Eliminate the Japanese and protect the country!

05:51.120 --> 05:53.880
Eliminate the Japanese and protect the country!

05:54.120 --> 05:56.800
Eliminate the Japanese and protect the country!

05:56.800 --> 05:59.360
Eliminate the Japanese and protect the country!

05:59.360 --> 06:01.960
Eliminate the Japanese and protect the country!

06:01.960 --> 06:04.690
Eliminate the Japanese and protect the country!

06:05.320 --> 06:06.120
Good!

06:06.200 --> 06:08.200
Good!

06:08.680 --> 06:11.160
Well acted!

06:11.440 --> 06:12.520
Well acted!

06:12.760 --> 06:13.560
Good!

06:14.080 --> 06:14.920
Good!

06:16.520 --> 06:19.320
Good!

06:20.320 --> 06:22.520
Xiaoyue, hurry up and pack your things.

06:23.720 --> 06:24.650
I have to go back.

06:25.120 --> 06:26.800
I'll make a special trip to see you another day,

06:26.800 --> 06:27.280
okay?

06:28.120 --> 06:30.680
Yue'er!

06:34.280 --> 06:35.240
You

06:35.640 --> 06:36.570
joined the army?

06:36.800 --> 06:37.680
Hello, Miss Yu.

06:39.080 --> 06:39.880
I'll help you.

06:41.440 --> 06:42.120
By the way,

06:42.400 --> 06:44.040
what is Miss Yu's plan?

06:45.000 --> 06:47.159
Our master plans to retreat to Wuhan.

06:47.360 --> 06:48.240
To Wuhan.

06:50.520 --> 06:52.400
Okay. Let me tell you, Xiaoyue,

06:52.520 --> 06:54.280
go wherever the Yu family goes.

06:54.400 --> 06:55.840
If they go to Wuhan, you go to Wuhan.

06:55.840 --> 06:56.440
Okay.

06:57.800 --> 06:59.360
Then, when the war is over here,

06:59.360 --> 07:00.280
I'll come find you.

07:00.280 --> 07:00.800
Don't worry.

07:00.800 --> 07:02.160
I'm safe with them.

07:02.400 --> 07:03.960
As for you, with all the fighting and killing,

07:03.960 --> 07:04.960
you must take good care of yourself.

07:04.960 --> 07:05.820
Did you hear me?

07:05.880 --> 07:07.520
Don't worry, I'm very smart.

07:07.600 --> 07:08.360
I'll be fine.

07:15.160 --> 07:16.480
These are my savings.

07:16.920 --> 07:17.760
Take them.

07:17.760 --> 07:18.320
Xiaoyue,

07:18.800 --> 07:19.120
hurry up,

07:19.120 --> 07:19.640
we have to catch the next show.

07:19.640 --> 07:20.800
No, I'm a soldier, I have money.

07:20.800 --> 07:21.840
What would I use this for?

07:21.840 --> 07:23.040
I don't need it. You keep it.

07:23.040 --> 07:23.840
Xiaoyue!

07:38.680 --> 07:39.360
Xiaoyue!

07:39.760 --> 07:40.360
Stop!

07:40.440 --> 07:41.159
Xiaoyue!

07:41.880 --> 07:42.480
Here,

07:42.920 --> 07:43.880
take it,

07:48.880 --> 07:49.960
put it on.

07:54.240 --> 07:55.280
Does it look good?

07:55.520 --> 07:56.440
Yes.

07:56.760 --> 07:58.440
Wait for me in Wuhan.

07:58.960 --> 07:59.920
Okay.

08:08.360 --> 08:09.200
Let's go.

08:16.600 --> 08:17.400
Let's go.

08:25.600 --> 08:26.440
Let's go.

08:34.000 --> 08:34.880
Any news?

08:35.280 --> 08:36.039
Not yet.

08:53.040 --> 08:55.100
Brigade Commander, it's time to eat.

09:40.360 --> 09:41.280
Father.

09:41.680 --> 09:43.280
Take a rest and have some tea.

09:45.800 --> 09:46.600
Master!

09:47.440 --> 09:48.360
Madam!

09:48.560 --> 09:49.560
We won the battle!

09:50.480 --> 09:51.520
We won!

09:52.920 --> 09:53.850
A great victory!

09:54.160 --> 09:54.800
Master,

09:56.240 --> 09:57.170
a great victory!

10:08.960 --> 10:11.620
The enemies have sent more troops to Wusongkou.

10:15.960 --> 10:16.640
Well,

10:16.880 --> 10:18.600
Yunkui hasn't been heard from for so long.

10:18.600 --> 10:19.840
Where is he now?

10:24.280 --> 10:25.240
Yujiao.

10:27.280 --> 10:29.480
Military forces have no constant formation,

10:29.480 --> 10:31.480
just as water has no constant shape.

10:31.840 --> 10:34.560
One who adapts to the enemy to win

10:35.120 --> 10:36.380
is considered divine.

10:40.600 --> 10:41.640
In times of war,

10:42.040 --> 10:43.440
military mail is blocked.

10:43.440 --> 10:45.640
Soldiers have no time to write home,

10:46.240 --> 10:49.160
and officers' movements are top secret.

10:49.640 --> 10:50.520
So,

10:50.800 --> 10:52.130
as for news from Yunkui,

10:52.720 --> 10:54.040
don't expect any.

10:55.280 --> 10:56.520
I know, Father.

10:58.160 --> 10:58.920
Look.

10:59.400 --> 11:00.960
Luodian,

11:01.760 --> 11:02.840
Yuepu,

11:03.200 --> 11:03.960
and Baoshan.

11:04.240 --> 11:06.770
The fighting along this line is quite fierce.

11:07.120 --> 11:07.680
Look.

11:07.760 --> 11:09.620
This is a triangular area, right?

11:09.920 --> 11:12.640
But if the Japanese army concentrates

11:12.760 --> 11:14.280
their sea, land, and air forces on one point

11:14.280 --> 11:15.280
to attack us,

11:15.840 --> 11:19.080
knowing our firepower is inferior,

11:19.200 --> 11:20.400
why do we still deploy

11:20.400 --> 11:22.320
a large number of troops here?

11:22.680 --> 11:23.680
It's not worth it.

11:23.800 --> 11:24.880
A miscalculation.

11:36.240 --> 11:37.200
Yujiao.

11:38.360 --> 11:40.040
You are pregnant.

11:40.280 --> 11:41.920
Don't think too much.

11:43.960 --> 11:44.720
Mrs. Liu.

11:45.080 --> 11:45.920
Master.

11:46.440 --> 11:47.570
Starting tomorrow,

11:47.960 --> 11:50.160
you need to add to Yujiao's chicken soup

11:50.160 --> 11:51.160
some astragalus.

11:51.760 --> 11:52.920
It invigorates the blood and replenishes Qi,

11:52.920 --> 11:54.080
and also boosts Yang.

11:54.080 --> 11:55.000
But not too much.

11:55.000 --> 11:55.800
Just six mace.

11:55.800 --> 11:56.560
Six mace.

11:58.280 --> 12:00.000
I still have a hen stewing on the stove.

12:00.000 --> 12:00.920
Oh, my old hen!

12:01.440 --> 12:02.500
Six mace. Six mace.

12:09.240 --> 12:10.080
Father.

12:10.200 --> 12:11.200
Yujiao,

12:11.520 --> 12:13.050
you are going to be a mother.

12:13.520 --> 12:15.680
You must relax and nourish your Qi.

12:17.160 --> 12:19.720
The calming method I taught you,

12:20.360 --> 12:21.360
have you tried it?

12:22.520 --> 12:23.160
Father,

12:23.720 --> 12:25.160
it's not that easy.

12:26.200 --> 12:28.920
Ever since the last air raid,

12:29.160 --> 12:31.620
I can't even stand the sound of horse hooves.

12:31.640 --> 12:32.880
Whenever I hear horse hooves,

12:32.880 --> 12:34.210
it reminds me of Yunkui.

12:35.560 --> 12:37.420
We were all running for our lives.

12:37.680 --> 12:40.010
Yunkui is desperately charging forward.

12:40.640 --> 12:42.770
It makes me sad just thinking about it.

12:43.560 --> 12:44.840
Don't be sad.

12:45.480 --> 12:46.680
Relax.

12:47.400 --> 12:48.440
Keep calm.

12:54.000 --> 12:55.920
Dad, the alarm is sounding again.

12:56.080 --> 12:58.080
Let's hurry to the air raid shelter.

12:58.520 --> 13:00.720
Mrs. Liu, Mrs. Liu!

13:02.040 --> 13:02.920
Ayi!

13:03.720 --> 13:05.120
Don't panic, Ayi.

13:07.080 --> 13:08.560
What did I just say?

13:10.120 --> 13:13.240
A gentleman is not a utensil.

13:15.520 --> 13:16.440
Not a utensil.

13:17.000 --> 13:18.080
I understand.

13:23.560 --> 13:24.960
Don't be angry.

13:25.000 --> 13:26.260
Please don't be angry.

13:28.880 --> 13:32.920
Ayi! Ayi!

13:33.920 --> 13:35.240
Ayi!

14:10.680 --> 14:12.280
Hello, this is Zhang Yunkui.

14:20.200 --> 14:21.000
Hello?

14:21.240 --> 14:21.960
Deputy Division Commander Liao.

14:21.960 --> 14:22.880
Three days after three days.

14:22.880 --> 14:25.410
When exactly will the 159th Division arrive?

14:25.480 --> 14:26.440
Yunkui.

14:26.720 --> 14:29.520
The 159th Division ran into difficulties on the way.

14:29.520 --> 14:30.640
The enemy has cut off

14:30.640 --> 14:32.960
communications between Liuzhen and you.

14:32.960 --> 14:34.680
Currently, the 159th Division

14:34.680 --> 14:36.720
is also under immense pressure in Liuzhen.

14:36.720 --> 14:37.600
But Liuzhen is

14:37.600 --> 14:39.080
only about thirty miles from here!

14:39.080 --> 14:40.800
Our communications have been cut off.

14:40.800 --> 14:42.360
The current situation is unclear.

14:42.360 --> 14:44.280
Yunkui, hold out for another three days.

14:44.280 --> 14:44.940
Three days.

14:45.000 --> 14:45.560
If they don't arrive in three days,

14:45.560 --> 14:46.680
it's their responsibility.

14:46.680 --> 14:47.560
What time is it now?

14:47.560 --> 14:49.160
Why are we talking about responsibility?

14:49.160 --> 14:51.020
Deputy Division Commander Liao,

14:52.200 --> 14:53.240
our entire brigade has over 6,000 men,

14:53.240 --> 14:54.360
and now there are only 400 left.

14:54.360 --> 14:55.800
We really can't hold out much longer.

14:55.800 --> 14:56.960
If this continues,

14:57.120 --> 14:58.880
the Japanese army will break through us sooner or later!

14:58.880 --> 15:00.160
Deputy Division Commander Liao,

15:00.160 --> 15:01.520
I request an active retreat.

15:01.520 --> 15:03.160
To retreat to Liuzhen, merge with the 159th Division,

15:03.160 --> 15:04.490
and strike back at them.

15:04.520 --> 15:06.760
The enemies will definitely think we are retreating in panic

15:06.760 --> 15:08.080
and will definitely underestimate us and advance rashly.

15:08.080 --> 15:09.480
Then we can rely on Liuzhen's

15:09.480 --> 15:10.560
solid fortifications

15:10.560 --> 15:11.600
to stop the enemies.

15:11.600 --> 15:14.040
Attack their advance troops from both flanks

15:14.040 --> 15:15.440
and catch them off guard.

15:19.040 --> 15:20.000
Impossible.

15:20.480 --> 15:22.280
Execute the order immediately!

15:36.520 --> 15:37.680
Staff Officer Xie,

15:38.360 --> 15:39.400
inform Commander Liu and Commander Feng to hold a meeting.

15:39.400 --> 15:40.360
Yes.

15:42.160 --> 15:44.120
The enemy is determined to win,

15:44.600 --> 15:47.080
and our army is determined to defend to the death.

15:47.080 --> 15:49.880
Unfortunately, the disparity in weapons is huge,

15:50.160 --> 15:53.440
and the higher-ups favor a passive, purely defensive strategy.

15:53.440 --> 15:56.400
This time moving to Baijiazai Town,

15:57.280 --> 15:59.520
the enemy's offensive is stronger,

16:00.000 --> 16:01.800
and the future is unpredictable.

16:01.800 --> 16:03.760
Fortunately, all officers and soldiers of our brigade

16:03.760 --> 16:07.200
are determined to live or die with Songhu.

16:08.600 --> 16:10.360
If Yunkui dies

16:10.840 --> 16:12.440
but Shanghai remains,

16:12.760 --> 16:15.120
my wish will be fulfilled.

16:21.760 --> 16:23.480
Father taught me that

16:23.680 --> 16:27.000
when loyalty and filial piety cannot be achieved at the same time,

16:27.000 --> 16:30.040
serving the country is filial piety.

16:30.560 --> 16:33.420
Therefore, I have no other thoughts in this battle,

16:34.160 --> 16:38.240
only asking you to take care of your health,

16:39.240 --> 16:43.760
and forgive me for not being able to fulfill my filial duties at your bedside.

16:45.040 --> 16:46.120
Yujiao,

16:46.440 --> 16:47.520
a soldier

16:47.800 --> 16:49.060
before a major battle,

16:49.440 --> 16:51.200
will write a suicide note

16:51.360 --> 16:53.080
to express his determination.

16:53.080 --> 16:54.920
Don't be sad.

16:55.240 --> 16:58.920
Yunkui is a soldier cultivated by the country.

16:59.440 --> 17:03.560
He is the descendant of the Chinese scholars for three thousand years.

17:04.000 --> 17:06.599
No matter what happens to him this time,

17:07.440 --> 17:09.920
dead or alive,

17:10.200 --> 17:13.400
we should all be proud of him.

17:14.000 --> 17:15.880
I will live well.

17:16.200 --> 17:17.160
And you,

17:17.560 --> 17:19.680
must take good care of yourself too.

17:20.280 --> 17:21.440
This way,

17:21.760 --> 17:24.400
Yunkui can feel at ease.

17:27.280 --> 17:28.840
Don't read the rest.

17:29.160 --> 17:31.120
That's all written for you.

17:33.240 --> 17:34.280
Father.

17:34.640 --> 17:35.840
Yunkui

17:36.360 --> 17:37.600
also asked you

17:37.920 --> 17:40.560
to name the unborn child.

17:40.560 --> 17:41.920
No rush.

17:43.040 --> 17:45.040
Let's wait for him to come back together

17:45.040 --> 17:47.160
to name the child.

17:50.040 --> 17:51.560
Thank you, Father.

17:57.280 --> 17:59.000
Sweet dreams.

18:00.040 --> 18:01.760
Sweet dreams.

19:11.720 --> 19:12.600
According to the reconnaissance,

19:12.600 --> 19:13.760
between us and Liuzhen,

19:13.760 --> 19:14.880
there is only one enemy squadron.

19:14.880 --> 19:15.210
Here.

19:15.480 --> 19:16.280
Here.

19:16.280 --> 19:18.080
It just happens to grab us by the neck.

19:18.080 --> 19:20.120
It's difficult for the 159th Division to come over.

19:20.120 --> 19:21.200
What are you thinking?

19:21.200 --> 19:22.440
There are so many Japs outside now.

19:22.440 --> 19:23.920
The 159th Division can barely protect itself.

19:23.920 --> 19:25.480
You still expect them to support us?

19:25.480 --> 19:26.200
Brigadier,

19:26.320 --> 19:27.520
give the order to retreat.

19:27.520 --> 19:28.520
If we don't retreat,

19:28.520 --> 19:29.960
all the brothers will be left here.

19:29.960 --> 19:31.480
The division commander's order is to hold.

19:31.480 --> 19:33.240
We can't hold out for three days.

19:33.240 --> 19:34.280
By tomorrow,

19:34.560 --> 19:36.280
four hundred people will be reduced to two hundred.

19:36.280 --> 19:38.880
By the day after tomorrow, they'll all be gone.

19:41.200 --> 19:42.160
Connect to the division headquarters.

19:42.160 --> 19:44.690
Brigadier, there is still a fault in the line.

19:45.360 --> 19:46.120
Brigadier.

19:46.200 --> 19:47.840
Why not send someone to the 159th Division?

19:47.840 --> 19:50.000
At least hold on for another day.

19:53.000 --> 19:54.200
It's too late.

19:55.360 --> 19:56.360
Prepare the horse.

19:56.360 --> 19:57.360
Yes, sir.

19:58.080 --> 19:59.040
I'm going to the division headquarters.

19:59.040 --> 20:00.120
Wait for my news.

22:05.840 --> 22:07.520
Commander of the 87th Brigade, Zhang Yunkui,

22:07.520 --> 22:08.840
reporting to you.

22:10.640 --> 22:11.840
Who told you to come?

22:13.120 --> 22:15.320
Didn't you order him to hold his ground?

22:16.200 --> 22:18.260
Division Commander, I came on my own.

22:18.480 --> 22:20.280
We really can't miss the opportunity again.

22:20.280 --> 22:20.960
The enemy in front of us

22:20.960 --> 22:22.200
will definitely underestimate us and advance rashly.

22:22.200 --> 22:23.360
I can pretend to retreat,

22:23.360 --> 22:24.280
lure the enemy in deep,

22:24.280 --> 22:25.120
then strike back

22:25.120 --> 22:26.400
and completely wipe them out.

22:26.400 --> 22:28.120
But if we hold our ground to the death,

22:28.120 --> 22:29.400
I'm afraid before the reinforcements arrive,

22:29.400 --> 22:30.840
we'll be completely wiped out.

22:30.840 --> 22:31.800
Zhang Yunkui,

22:32.120 --> 22:33.320
this is a military order from the war zone.

22:33.320 --> 22:35.400
It's not your place to make irresponsible remarks.

22:35.400 --> 22:37.320
Just because you are absent from your post without permission now,

22:37.320 --> 22:39.000
I can shoot you right now.

22:41.560 --> 22:43.080
I used to be your chief of staff.

22:43.080 --> 22:44.560
Now I'm your brigade commander.

22:44.560 --> 22:45.720
You know what kind of person I am.

22:45.720 --> 22:46.680
I'm not doing this for myself.

22:46.680 --> 22:47.600
I'm doing this for our army,

22:47.600 --> 22:48.600
for our division.

22:48.680 --> 22:51.080
You are neither the division commander nor the army commander.

22:51.080 --> 22:54.740
You should go back and execute your military orders immediately.

23:02.280 --> 23:03.160
Yunkui.

23:07.080 --> 23:07.960
Commander.

23:08.080 --> 23:09.560
Yunkui is not afraid of death,

23:09.560 --> 23:12.040
but we really can't delay military operations anymore.

23:12.040 --> 23:13.440
So I implore you to approve me

23:13.440 --> 23:14.240
to go to Liu Town

23:14.240 --> 23:15.970
to support the 159th Division.

23:35.760 --> 23:37.480
Yunkui, you go back first.

23:37.720 --> 23:39.480
I will ask for instructions from the superiors.

23:39.480 --> 23:40.560
If before ten o'clock tonight

23:40.560 --> 23:42.040
you haven't received a call,

23:42.040 --> 23:43.120
you go.

23:45.120 --> 23:46.480
Yes.

23:55.480 --> 23:55.960
Commander.

23:55.960 --> 23:56.440
Commander,

23:56.440 --> 23:57.400
look at this.

24:35.240 --> 24:36.800
Little mouse climbs the lampstand,

24:36.800 --> 24:37.660
can't get down.

25:11.600 --> 25:13.000
Mom, I'm scared.

25:13.480 --> 25:14.480
Don't be scared, baby.

25:14.480 --> 25:16.080
Mom is here, don't be scared.

25:17.080 --> 25:18.840
Today there were more than 30 planes,

25:18.840 --> 25:20.280
all flying from Shanghai.

25:20.280 --> 25:21.400
They bombed our radio station,

25:21.400 --> 25:22.130
water plant,

25:22.240 --> 25:23.520
and military departments.

25:23.520 --> 25:25.320
Who said they only bombed these?

25:25.400 --> 25:27.040
My cousin lives on Fuxi Street.

25:27.040 --> 25:28.040
In the afternoon,

25:28.040 --> 25:30.600
two out of three courtyards of his house were destroyed.

25:30.600 --> 25:32.360
My uncle, aunt, and cousin

25:32.840 --> 25:34.080
were all bombed to death.

25:34.080 --> 25:35.200
The devils

25:35.640 --> 25:37.720
suffered a big loss in Shanghai.

25:38.160 --> 25:39.360
Revenge.

25:39.880 --> 25:42.160
Taking revenge on civilians.

25:42.480 --> 25:44.680
This only shows they are incompetent

25:45.000 --> 25:45.880
and cowardly.

25:46.280 --> 25:47.000
Yes,

25:47.160 --> 25:48.240
the old gentleman is right.

25:48.240 --> 25:50.120
Yes, that makes sense.

25:50.320 --> 25:51.040
Cowardly.

25:51.040 --> 25:54.160
Whom the gods would destroy, they first make mad.

25:54.360 --> 25:55.690
They also speak wildly,

25:55.880 --> 25:58.720
saying they will occupy China in three months.

25:59.080 --> 26:01.160
In their dreams!

26:01.360 --> 26:02.520
Nonsense.

26:04.440 --> 26:05.480
Drive them all out.

26:05.480 --> 26:06.080
Nonsense.

26:06.080 --> 26:07.080
Japanese devils.

26:07.760 --> 26:09.360
These little Japanese are very bad.

26:09.360 --> 26:09.920
Really.

26:09.920 --> 26:11.080
Trapped here,

26:11.080 --> 26:13.140
we can't even see the moon on the 15th.

26:18.480 --> 26:20.400
Will we be crushed

26:20.560 --> 26:22.800
and hit by bombs?

26:22.880 --> 26:23.920
No.

26:23.920 --> 26:25.240
Is it really going to collapse?

26:25.240 --> 26:25.960
Mom, look,

26:25.960 --> 26:28.320
the moon is so round.

26:30.040 --> 26:30.960
Yes,

26:31.080 --> 26:32.140
it's big and round,

26:32.440 --> 26:33.960
right?

26:45.640 --> 26:46.840
Today is August 15th.

26:47.000 --> 26:48.440
I have a box of mooncakes here.

26:48.440 --> 26:49.880
Let's all have a taste.

26:50.120 --> 26:52.200
Yes, I'll treat everyone to tangyuan too.

26:52.200 --> 26:54.040
I'll treat everyone to wontons.

26:54.360 --> 26:56.080
Help me distribute them to everyone.

26:56.080 --> 26:57.320
Have a mooncake.

26:57.400 --> 26:58.520
Give them to everyone.

26:58.520 --> 26:59.560
Okay. Thank you, thank you, thank you.

26:59.560 --> 27:01.290
Are you guys eating mooncakes?

27:01.600 --> 27:02.800
Yes, thank you.

27:22.360 --> 27:23.890
Last Mid-Autumn Festival,

27:24.080 --> 27:26.680
Zuliang, many of our classmates, and I

27:26.800 --> 27:28.960
admired the moon together at the Bund.

27:31.040 --> 27:33.500
I wonder if Zuliang has any mooncakes to eat.

27:34.680 --> 27:36.720
I wonder where Wanfu is.

27:39.440 --> 27:41.320
Does he have any mooncakes?

27:41.880 --> 27:43.360
Silly girl,

27:44.040 --> 27:47.280
don't you always praise Wanfu for being smart,

27:47.440 --> 27:48.920
clever, and adaptable?

27:49.280 --> 27:51.880
He will definitely be safe.

27:59.360 --> 28:01.600
To Division Commander Sun Huaiyi,

28:02.920 --> 28:06.040
My 6,000 fine men have all been sacrificed.

28:06.920 --> 28:08.560
If the position is held,

28:08.760 --> 28:11.040
I shall survive to see you,

28:11.040 --> 28:12.840
and apologize for my offense.

28:14.440 --> 28:15.920
If the position is lost,

28:16.280 --> 28:17.480
I shall die in battle,

28:17.520 --> 28:19.440
and my body will be left in the wilderness.

28:19.440 --> 28:21.480
One day, after the victory of the war,

28:21.480 --> 28:23.080
you will be a famous general.

28:23.280 --> 28:24.560
When you drive through Shanghai,

28:24.560 --> 28:26.800
if you hear the wind blowing through the pines like the sea,

28:26.800 --> 28:28.600
that will be me coming to see you.

28:29.320 --> 28:31.440
The 6,000 lonely souls behind me

28:31.680 --> 28:34.880
will also smile in the underworld.

28:41.800 --> 28:42.920
Brigade Commander,

28:42.920 --> 28:44.840
I made some food for you.

28:51.240 --> 28:53.300
It's the Mid-Autumn Festival today.

28:58.400 --> 28:59.240
Erbao.

29:02.600 --> 29:05.400
Did you just say today is the Mid-Autumn Festival?

29:06.480 --> 29:07.320
Look.

29:22.800 --> 29:23.600
Mooncakes.

29:24.680 --> 29:25.520
I made them.

29:27.040 --> 29:28.200
Do the brothers have them?

29:28.200 --> 29:29.240
They all do.

29:29.600 --> 29:30.840
It's a big festival,

29:31.040 --> 29:33.640
so the brothers have something to think about.

29:35.880 --> 29:37.040
Don't break it.

29:37.080 --> 29:38.640
I made this with water caltrops.

29:38.640 --> 29:40.300
It'll shatter if you break it.

29:41.120 --> 29:42.960
Catch it.

29:53.080 --> 29:53.920
Is it good?

29:54.920 --> 29:55.850
It's delicious.

29:57.400 --> 30:00.600
How did you think of using water caltrops for the filling?

30:00.640 --> 30:02.240
Don't we have nothing left?

30:02.680 --> 30:03.960
I saw that the pond next to our position

30:03.960 --> 30:05.680
was full of water caltrops.

30:05.760 --> 30:06.400
So I thought,

30:06.400 --> 30:08.260
could I mash these water caltrops

30:08.400 --> 30:09.320
into mooncakes?

30:09.320 --> 30:10.880
I didn't expect it to work.

30:11.240 --> 30:12.440
It was just too rushed.

30:12.440 --> 30:15.040
I spent a long time on this water caltrop dough.

30:15.240 --> 30:16.800
You know the shape of this mooncake,

30:16.800 --> 30:19.440
I formed it with fired artillery shells.

30:19.880 --> 30:20.800
You have no idea.

30:20.800 --> 30:21.960
Those fired artillery shells

30:21.960 --> 30:23.840
were either rotten or flat.

30:24.120 --> 30:25.080
It wasn't easy for me

30:25.080 --> 30:26.360
to find a round one.

30:26.480 --> 30:27.800
It had to be me.

30:28.440 --> 30:29.960
Anyway, when we get to Shanghai,

30:29.960 --> 30:31.800
I'll make you an authentic mooncake,

30:31.800 --> 30:33.200
with date paste filling.

30:33.280 --> 30:36.410
I guarantee it will taste better than Guanshengyuan's.

30:40.200 --> 30:41.440
Drink some water.

30:45.640 --> 30:46.770
Brigade Commander,

30:46.920 --> 30:48.680
I have another good thing here.

30:52.520 --> 30:53.780
Where did it come from?

30:54.400 --> 30:55.640
Weren't we digging trenches?

30:55.640 --> 30:57.400
We tore down two houses on the edge of town,

30:57.400 --> 30:59.930
and found several jars buried under the wall.

31:01.080 --> 31:02.400
Grab a mug too.

31:13.400 --> 31:15.000
Happy Mid-Autumn Festival.

31:16.000 --> 31:17.860
Happy Mid-Autumn Festival, sir.

31:21.280 --> 31:22.280
Good wine.

31:22.960 --> 31:24.640
Let's go to the frontline.

31:25.480 --> 31:26.480
Come here, Erbao,

31:26.720 --> 31:28.120
help me take off my boots.

31:51.240 --> 31:52.880
How did you tie these puttees?

31:52.880 --> 31:54.000
I don't know how.

31:54.040 --> 31:56.240
Three turns forward, three turns back,

31:56.400 --> 31:58.120
press down the scales and three turns forward,

31:58.120 --> 32:00.580
then tuck the end of the string into the seam.

32:02.120 --> 32:03.080
Tie it again.

32:06.760 --> 32:07.680
Erbao.

32:08.800 --> 32:09.760
The wine we just tasted

32:09.760 --> 32:11.520
should be Lanling Xiang, right?

32:11.520 --> 32:12.360
Brigadier,

32:12.640 --> 32:14.170
you know so much about wine.

32:14.320 --> 32:15.580
That is Lanling Amber.

32:15.920 --> 32:17.800
Have you heard a poem by Li Bai?

32:18.200 --> 32:20.400
'Lanling's fine wine smells of tulips,

32:20.640 --> 32:22.960
amber light shining in the jade cup.'

32:23.080 --> 32:24.740
It's talking about this wine.

32:24.840 --> 32:26.600
Amber light shining in the jade bowl.

32:26.600 --> 32:27.640
You even know Li Bai?

32:27.640 --> 32:29.320
This is the wine from our hometown.

32:29.320 --> 32:31.450
Everyone in our hometown knows Li Bai.

32:31.720 --> 32:33.050
Isn't it a coincidence?

32:33.160 --> 32:33.920
I actually found

32:33.920 --> 32:35.680
the wine from our hometown here.

32:35.680 --> 32:36.840
This is destiny.

32:37.240 --> 32:38.640
The one we just drank

32:38.920 --> 32:41.320
is the Xun family's Lanling Amber.

32:41.640 --> 32:42.640
The Wang family's

32:42.800 --> 32:44.440
is called Lanling Yizui.

32:44.720 --> 32:45.840
The one from Mengjiazhuang

32:45.840 --> 32:47.440
is called Lanling Yujin.

32:48.480 --> 32:51.280
With just one sentence from old man Li Bai,

32:51.440 --> 32:52.880
the people in our hometown

32:52.880 --> 32:54.940
have had food to eat for generations.

32:55.040 --> 32:56.760
We have good wine in our hometown too.

32:56.760 --> 32:57.560
It's just that

32:57.600 --> 32:58.460
it came out late

32:58.960 --> 33:00.800
and didn't catch the Poetry Immortal's eye.

33:00.800 --> 33:02.920
Brigadier, you can also write a poem.

33:03.320 --> 33:04.200
Is it tied yet?

33:04.400 --> 33:05.560
Almost.

33:06.000 --> 33:07.960
It seems tighter than before.

33:16.880 --> 33:17.520
Let me see.

33:17.720 --> 33:18.280
No way.

33:18.280 --> 33:19.400
Attention!

33:23.960 --> 33:25.640
Align this.

33:27.320 --> 33:28.400
Then tie it in the middle.

33:28.400 --> 33:29.600
A bit tighter,

33:30.600 --> 33:32.000
and tuck it into the seam.

33:32.920 --> 33:33.960
This leg.

33:37.920 --> 33:38.760
Done.

33:39.640 --> 33:40.770
Go to the front line.

33:52.080 --> 33:52.680
Here.

33:53.280 --> 33:54.160
Happy Mid-Autumn Festival.

33:54.160 --> 33:55.020
Thank you, sir.

33:56.520 --> 33:57.200
Happy Mid-Autumn Festival.

33:57.200 --> 33:58.240
We even have mooncakes to eat.

33:58.240 --> 33:58.960
Not bad.

33:59.120 --> 34:00.520
We have mooncakes to eat.

34:01.200 --> 34:02.000
Thank you.

34:03.920 --> 34:05.560
Have one, take it.

34:05.840 --> 34:07.170
Water caltrop filling.

34:07.240 --> 34:08.840
Happy Mid-Autumn Festival.

34:08.920 --> 34:09.920
Here.

34:09.920 --> 34:10.920
Eat the mooncake.

34:21.199 --> 34:21.840
Good job.

34:22.000 --> 34:22.880
Thank you, Colonel.

34:22.880 --> 34:24.159
Good job.

34:25.520 --> 34:27.360
Blind man, sing a song

34:27.560 --> 34:28.690
to lighten the mood.

34:29.480 --> 34:30.480
It really works.

34:59.080 --> 34:59.840
Brigadier.

35:00.000 --> 35:00.720
Brigadier.

35:05.600 --> 35:07.920
Brigadier, Brigadier.

35:18.160 --> 35:20.960
I'm Liu Yishou from Shanxi.

35:21.320 --> 35:23.560
Today, I'll sing a Shanxi folk song for everyone.

35:23.560 --> 35:24.290
Sounds good?

35:24.360 --> 35:25.640
Good!

35:25.920 --> 35:29.440
A stretch of willow trees on the beach,

35:29.680 --> 35:33.160
turning yellow leaf by leaf.

35:33.440 --> 35:38.640
Clusters of sweet dates,

35:38.920 --> 35:42.240
so red, so red.

35:42.680 --> 35:45.840
Bowls of apricot blossom wine,

35:46.120 --> 35:49.320
mellow with every sip.

35:49.840 --> 35:54.560
Jars of aged vinegar,

35:55.440 --> 35:58.920
sour enough to kill a man.

35:58.920 --> 36:00.760
Good.

36:01.040 --> 36:01.720
Excuse me.

36:02.120 --> 36:03.360
I've made a fool of myself.

36:03.360 --> 36:04.240
Good.

36:04.240 --> 36:05.200
Commander.

36:05.280 --> 36:06.360
Stand up!

36:07.000 --> 36:08.400
Salute!

36:10.640 --> 36:11.480
At ease.

36:11.520 --> 36:12.850
Sit down. Keep singing.

36:13.920 --> 36:15.200
Keep singing.

36:17.440 --> 36:18.440
Sit down.

36:19.920 --> 36:21.880
You were singing so well just now.

36:22.240 --> 36:23.400
Why did you stop?

36:23.600 --> 36:24.960
Well, the Commander is here.

36:24.960 --> 36:26.640
Let's have the Commander sing a song, how about it?

36:26.640 --> 36:27.080
Good.

36:27.080 --> 36:27.520
Commander, sing a song!

36:27.520 --> 36:28.120
All right.

36:28.120 --> 36:28.720
Commander, sing a song!

36:28.720 --> 36:29.920
Sing one!

36:30.080 --> 36:33.080
Sing one!

36:33.400 --> 36:35.840
Sing one!

36:36.000 --> 36:38.800
Sing one!

36:38.800 --> 36:40.520
Sing one!

36:40.520 --> 36:42.280
All right.

36:45.960 --> 36:47.960
I couldn't sing when I was in school.

36:48.360 --> 36:49.760
But influenced by my father,

36:49.760 --> 36:52.080
I can recite poetry a little.

36:52.600 --> 36:53.560
Today is the Mid-Autumn Festival.

36:53.560 --> 36:55.440
I'll recite a piece from Su Shi's

36:55.840 --> 36:56.770
'Water Melody',

36:57.000 --> 36:57.360
okay?

36:57.360 --> 36:58.280
Good.

37:00.560 --> 37:02.000
Don't laugh at me.

37:05.880 --> 37:10.480
When will the bright moon appear?

37:11.560 --> 37:15.360
With a cup of wine in my hand, I ask the blue sky.

37:15.960 --> 37:20.760
I don't know what season it would be

37:21.360 --> 37:25.720
in the heavens on this night.

37:26.400 --> 37:31.280
I'd like to ride the wind to fly home.

37:32.240 --> 37:36.840
Yet I fear the crystal and jade mansions

37:37.520 --> 37:42.960
are much too high and cold for me.

37:57.920 --> 37:58.480
Good.

37:58.640 --> 37:59.840
Good.

38:00.160 --> 38:01.080
Good.

38:02.200 --> 38:03.800
Good.

38:04.920 --> 38:05.840
Wu Youcai.

38:06.080 --> 38:08.000
You wear glasses, looking quite educated.

38:08.000 --> 38:09.160
Sing a song.

38:10.960 --> 38:12.360
I can't sing much either.

38:12.640 --> 38:13.720
I'm from Rehe.

38:13.920 --> 38:17.320
So I'll sing a local opera for you.

38:20.200 --> 38:23.720
In the mid-autumn of August,

38:23.720 --> 38:25.040
Erbao.

38:27.600 --> 38:29.680
Is there a problem with my singing?

38:29.680 --> 38:30.480
Yes,

38:30.760 --> 38:32.920
it's awful and I couldn't understand it.

38:32.920 --> 38:39.000
Errand boys are away from home,

38:40.520 --> 38:47.000
always facing three un-returns.

38:49.320 --> 38:52.120
First un-return:

38:53.760 --> 39:03.400
unable to show filial piety to parents.

39:03.400 --> 39:06.280
Second un-return:

39:07.200 --> 39:11.840
unable to accompany

39:13.120 --> 39:18.240
the wife by the bed.

39:18.720 --> 39:22.040
Third un-return:

39:22.360 --> 39:25.920
falling ill in a

39:31.000 --> 39:33.520
Third un-return:

39:34.160 --> 39:41.920
falling ill in a merchant inn.

39:57.760 --> 39:58.760
How is the radio?

39:58.880 --> 40:00.480
Commander, the electron tube is broken.

40:00.480 --> 40:01.640
We can't fix it without parts,

40:01.640 --> 40:03.840
and the telephone line was also bombed.

40:11.960 --> 40:12.720
It's too late.

40:12.720 --> 40:13.850
I must go to Liuzhen.

40:14.000 --> 40:14.920
Organize a reinforced platoon.

40:14.920 --> 40:16.040
We set off in two hours.

40:16.040 --> 40:18.080
Brigadier, you need to stay in command here.

40:18.080 --> 40:18.800
I should go.

40:18.960 --> 40:19.600
Let me go.

40:19.760 --> 40:20.680
Don't argue with me.

40:20.680 --> 40:21.520
I am the highest-ranking officer.

40:21.520 --> 40:22.120
Only if I go

40:22.280 --> 40:24.740
can we possibly bring back reinforcements.

40:29.640 --> 40:30.400
Brothers!

40:30.560 --> 40:31.520
Sir!

40:32.080 --> 40:33.760
The battle has come to this point.

40:33.760 --> 40:34.680
You all see it.

40:35.080 --> 40:36.880
I have no one else to use now.

40:37.360 --> 40:38.690
Going to Liuzhen with me

40:39.080 --> 40:40.210
means only one word.

40:40.920 --> 40:41.960
Death.

40:42.800 --> 40:43.760
Among you,

40:44.240 --> 40:46.370
I know some were conscripted by force.

40:46.720 --> 40:48.400
You are not real soldiers.

40:49.120 --> 40:50.600
You have no training

40:51.240 --> 40:52.770
and don't know how to fight.

40:53.040 --> 40:54.080
So,

40:54.400 --> 40:56.480
you don't have to die with us.

40:57.040 --> 40:58.170
If you want to leave,

40:58.920 --> 40:59.850
I won't stop you.

41:00.400 --> 41:01.600
Put down your gear

41:02.160 --> 41:03.680
and leave.

41:13.680 --> 41:14.440
Xiazi.

41:15.520 --> 41:16.360
Kong Erbao.

41:17.200 --> 41:18.200
Here.

41:20.360 --> 41:22.000
I forced you to stay

41:22.440 --> 41:23.800
and watch us die

41:24.280 --> 41:25.480
for one purpose only.

41:25.760 --> 41:26.820
I want to prove that

41:27.040 --> 41:28.680
Chinese soldiers

41:28.960 --> 41:30.280
are competent.

41:32.480 --> 41:33.840
Today is the Mid-Autumn Festival.

41:33.840 --> 41:35.560
You used every method you could think of

41:35.560 --> 41:36.800
to make mooncakes

41:36.920 --> 41:38.200
for all of us soldiers.

41:38.400 --> 41:40.000
We ate the mooncakes,

41:40.160 --> 41:41.220
looked at the moon,

41:41.760 --> 41:42.920
and we were happy.

41:43.440 --> 41:44.840
So all of us

41:45.240 --> 41:46.160
thank you.

41:47.640 --> 41:48.440
Kong Erbao.

41:48.800 --> 41:51.160
You are worthy of the name

41:51.560 --> 41:52.400
'Chinese'.

41:54.560 --> 41:56.220
Pour wine for everyone later,

41:56.280 --> 41:57.280
and you can leave

41:57.920 --> 41:59.120
to find your fiancée.

41:59.600 --> 42:00.800
But if all of us

42:00.800 --> 42:01.600
die in battle

42:02.040 --> 42:03.640
and you survive,

42:04.440 --> 42:05.920
I ask one thing of you.

42:06.880 --> 42:08.800
You must pass on a good name

42:08.880 --> 42:10.940
for the brothers of the 87th Brigade.

42:11.240 --> 42:11.970
Understood?

42:12.000 --> 42:13.200
Understood.

42:13.680 --> 42:14.480
Pour the wine.

42:14.520 --> 42:16.200
Yes, sir.

42:33.800 --> 42:34.930
I leave the position

42:35.760 --> 42:36.760
to you two.

42:37.280 --> 42:39.080
Rest assured, Brigade Commander.

42:39.080 --> 42:40.920
As long as I'm here, the position stands.

42:40.920 --> 42:42.080
I am a soldier.

42:42.680 --> 42:44.640
My uniform is my coffin.

42:50.560 --> 42:51.880
The Brigade Commander said

42:51.880 --> 42:52.840
one word:

42:53.280 --> 42:54.240
Death.

42:55.040 --> 42:56.440
Then we die.

43:00.520 --> 43:01.280
Brothers!

43:01.560 --> 43:02.600
Here!
